# School of Law, Governance & Public Order

## Purpose
Provides foundational education in governance, policy analysis, organizational compliance, and civic systems to support careers in law-adjacent and administrative roles.

## Scope
- legal foundations, nonprofit governance, policy writing, compliance documentation
- Credentials: pre-law track, MA-style professional programs, certificates
- Delivery: online/hybrid

## Distinctives
- Document drafting labs (policies, bylaws, governance records)
- Scenario-based policy and ethics analysis